deck: L'Wit is the daughter of the Brother Royal of the Badoon. Her life was spared and she was sent away for safety.
description:
Origin

L'Wit is the daughter of the Brother Royal of the Badoon and the loveliest of his royal harem. She convinced him to spare the daughter and she was shipped off as a baby where no one would ever seek her - Ubliex - a planet within the event horizon of a black hole.

She became a runner for a drug called comet dust and became as tough and skilled as the streets found necessary.

After Thanos allowed Gamora to kill the Badoon royal bloodline as revenge for the extinction of her own race, the remaining Badoon sought her out to regain power over the empire.
name: L'Wit

deck: Mysterious assassin with energy-emitting prosthetic hand. He was hired by criminal Mr. Kramer to kill Jasmine Destine also known as Cuckoo of Clan Destine.
description:
History

Skyline Killer was an assassin, who was hired by criminal Mr. Kramer, the financial director of Kay Cera's business empire to kidnapp and kill Jasmine Destine (alias - Kay Cera) also known as Cuckoo of Clan Destine to prevent her from inheriting her mother's fortune. Skyline Killer then captured Cuckoo and her sister Samantha Destine (Argent), but Spider-Man, Crimson Crusader and Imp arrived and defeated villain. Later Skyline Killer kidnapped and killed Mr. Kramer, because he have crossed him. The vigilante Punisher saw this and shot Skyline Killer, as a result killing him.

Powers and Abilities

His right hand was replaced with an prosthesis with claws. With his prosthetic hand, Skyline Killer could generate an unknown form of energy capable of explosions of huge force. Skyline Killer also possesses the normal strength of a man of his age, height, and build who engages in regular exercise.
name: Skyline Killer
